Jeanette Chabalala, News24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; A Gauteng police officer, his wife, and their two children were shot dead on Tuesday evening, police said. The 40-year-old police constable and his family were gunned down in their home in Makau near Ga-Rankuwa in Pretoria, police spokesperson Brigadier Sabatha Mokgwabone told News24 on Wednesday. The suspects fled the scene in the officer&rsquo;s vehicle, which was later found abandoned in another section of the village, Mokgwabone said.&nbsp; The family members were declared dead on scene. The officer's children were aged 3 and 22.Police were withholding their names until all family members had been notified. The constable was stationed at the Hebron police station, he said.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No arrests had yet been made.The motive for the shooting was unknown.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.